560
00:42:31,480 --> 00:42:35,480
Never kill a snake with your bare hands.

561
00:42:35,480 --> 00:42:36,480
It talks by hand.

562
00:42:36,480 --> 00:42:39,480
Yes, the sound spectrograph allows linguistic scientists

563
00:42:39,480 --> 00:42:42,480
to make very rapid studies of speech sounds.

564
00:42:42,480 --> 00:42:45,480
And among other things, some deaf people

565
00:42:45,480 --> 00:42:47,480
have been taught to see speech.

566
00:42:47,480 --> 00:42:52,480
For example, they learn to recognize this pattern as five.

567
00:42:52,480 --> 00:42:54,480
They hear with their eyes.

568
00:42:54,480 --> 00:42:58,480
Precisely, they see pictures of speech.

569
00:42:58,480 --> 00:43:01,480
Oh, we've got machines that talk to man

570
00:43:01,480 --> 00:43:04,480
and even machines that can listen.

571
00:43:04,480 --> 00:43:08,480
Audrey, that's a machine that listens to spoken numbers

572
00:43:08,480 --> 00:43:11,480
like a telephone operator and obeys orders.

573
00:43:11,480 --> 00:43:13,480
Four.

574
00:43:13,480 --> 00:43:15,480
Four.

